gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 138, Magic 135
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Magic, 138-135, in double overtime. Malik Monk led the Kings with a season-high 37 points and seven 3PT FG, along with nine assists as Keegan Murray (28 points, 12 rebounds) and Domantas Sabonis (22 points, 23 rebounds, 12 assists) totaled 50 points. Paolo Banchero totaled a career-high 43 points (six 3PT), four rebounds, and five assists as Jalen Suggs added 24 points (career-high six 3PT), three rebounds, and four assists. The Kings improve to 20-13 as the Magic move to 19-15.
